This paper discusses fundamental concepts in reinforcement learning (RL) and their theoretical analyses, making it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also addresses issues related to state resetting and Monte-Carlo Tree Search, which are commonly used in Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the verifiability of theoretical assumptions from data, which is relevant to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
